[mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `boto3` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `boto3` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `boto3` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in [releases](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder/releases). ## versioning `mypy-boto3-qconnect` documentation_summary: The HTML text introduces "mypy-boto3-qconnect," a Python package available on PyPI, designed to provide type annotations for the boto3.QConnect service. Released on January 19, 2024, version 1.34.23 of this package is generated with mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.1 and requires Python version 3.8 or higher. It is licensed under the MIT License and developed by Vlad Emelianov. The package aims to enhance code quality and developer productivity by offering explicit type annotations, client and paginator annotations, literals, and type definitions compatible with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright. Installation instructions are provided for different environments and IDEs, emphasizing the ease of integrating type checking and code completion for AWS Boto3 services.
